cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY

This paper discusses the dynamics of knowledge acquisition in complex networks, which is a topic related to information retrieval, machine learning, and data analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses network models and proposes different dynamics, which are related to machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the storage and organization of knowledge, which is related to cs.SD (Software Development) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
